{
  "texts": [
    "-GAN utilizes the advantage of VAE in alleviating the mode collapse problem in 3D MR image generation.",
    "The authors of Kwon et al. (2019) proposed an Autoencoding GAN and generated 3D MR images with different latent input z sizes like 100, 1000, and 2048.",
    "With a latent vector input of 1000, the proposed Auto-encoding GAN can generate diverse image samples while it fails to escape mode collapse with too small (100) or too large (2048) latent vector input sizes.",
    "To evaluate the diversity of synthetic images, authors Kwon et al. (2019) calculated average MMD × 10 -4 and MS-SSIM scores.",
    "The results show that the proposed GAN can perform better with a latent input value of 1000 with an average MMD × 10 -4 score of Fig. 18 The architecture of VAEGAN."
  ]
}